<div id="css" class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section-header">CSS</h2>
  <h3>BEM (Block Element Modifier)</h3>
  <p>BEM is a naming convention for your CSS classes to give them more meaning to other developers. More Information can be found <a href="http://csswizardry.com/2013/01/mindbemding-getting-your-head-round-bem-syntax/" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>
  <p>The naming convention follows this pattern:</p>
  <div class="code">
  {{#markdown}}
  ```css
  .block {}
  .block__element {}
  .block--modifier {}
  ```
  {{/markdown}}
  </div>

  <h3>SASS</h3>
  <p>SASS if used as a CSS pre-processor on bethesda. SASS adds functionality to basic css writting, making repetitive tasks quicker.</p>
  <h4>SASS Variables</h4>
  <p>SASS variables allow for customization of the site elements.</p>
  <div class="code">
  {{#markdown}}
  ```sass
  // widths
  $max-width: 1170px;
  ```
  {{/markdown}}
  </div>
</div> <!-- end docs-section -->

